Yobe State governor Hon Mai Mala Buni, on Thursday visited the minister of Finance Hajiya Zainab Shamsuna Ahmed in her office in Abuja. The governor discussed among other issues commitment of the federal and state governments to facilities and infrastructural development in the state. A statement issued by the director-general, Press and Media Affairs to the governor, Alhaji Mamman Mohammed, said the meeting centered on mutual cooperation between the federal government and state government. “The meeting considered areas of mutual cooperation that are beneficial to the people of the state and Nigerians generally,” he said. According to the statement, Governor Buni will continue to pursue more federal presence in the state. “His Excellency has continued to pursue and attract federal presence to the state for the benefit of our people,” the statement further said.